b'Hair Heads was a three part sketch that (spoiler alert) probably cost thousands of dollars worth of crystals and glass.  Jude Law was EXCELLENT in this sketch.'

b'HAIR HEADS.  Jude Law is the proud owner of a fine crystals store.  On opening night, the celebration is interrupted by two hair heads (Wiig, Forte) who, if frightened, will destroy everything on the shelves.  What is a hair head?  You would have to see it to understand.'
b"She was so good I assumed Natalie spoke Spanish but then I found out she didn't.  Turns out she's just excellent at her job."

b'TOY COLLECTORS.  Horatio and Fred are toy collectors who only speak Spanish.  Natalie Portman is a bilingual comic book store employee who helps them order figurines of, among others, Hanson Brothers, Todd McFarlane Spawn and Kiss.'
b'Every time I think about this sketch I wish that Wiig and Barkley had done 50 movies together.'

b'GRIEF COUNSELORS.  Wiig and Charles Barkley are grief counselors hired to cheer up an office who lose a co-worker.  At one point they put a pair of wind up chattering teeth on a desk and ask people to watch it while they take a break.  Barkley has piano keys on his sleeve.'

b'GABE KAPLAN.  Will Ferrell plays a man who loves and dresses like Gabe Kaplan.  He overhears people talking about how Gabe Kaplan came into to office earlier that day.  The entire sketch is his disbelief that no one came to get him.'
b"I was on SNL for 12.5 years.  It's not something I like to talk about much, but I assure you it's true.  ON TO MY WISH LIST!!!!"

b"For those who don't know, SECOND CHANCE THEATER is an insanely popular segment on our show in which we stage SNL sketches that were cut from dress.  It's so popular we have done it 6 times in 1008 shows."

b'The purpose of this thread (my first by the way) is to let anyone who is a fan of Adam or Sarah know that they are good people.  And not just to me.  All I have ever heard about them since the first time I heard their names is that they were good people.'
b"This weekend Sarah received a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame.  I am so happy for her.  She's been great forever."

b'Then, for real, she asked us if we played Wiffle Ball and when we said yes she pulled a bat and some balls out of her trunk and we played in the parking lot until someone came out and asked us to stop.'

b'And BEFORE I was on SNL I was living in LA with my brother.  We had just seen a friend perform at a comedy club and on the way to our car saw Sarah in the parking lot.  We introduced ourselves and she warmly exclaimed, "My parents told me there were some Bedford boys in town!"'

b"I sat in his office and he asked me about my upbringing and gave me sage and kind words about SNL that I never forgot.  He's the best.  A few years ago Adam was on Late Night and we talked about growing up in the same place.  It's one of my favorite interviews."

b'But here\'s the important part.  After I was hired at SNL I had a general meeting with one of the executives at Adam\'s production company Happy Madison.  I had no expectation of meeting Adam but on the way out the door I heard his familiar voice bellow, "Get that NH kid in here!\''

b'But then, just a few years later, Sarah Silverman was hired on SNL and she was from Bedford proper!  No one I knew had ever met Adam but I had friend who had met Sarah.  Watching her first weekend update feature gave me goosebumps.'

b'Adam was in a sketch called "What\'s the Best Way" about New Englanders giving directions. https://t.co/tY89jwaeTo There was a reference to the Jordan Marsh in Bedford.  At the time hearing my hometown on SNL was the most exciting thing that had ever happened to me.'

b'In H.S. I saw Adam do a set on Letterman https://t.co/xueyheeE36 I would have loved it no matter what but I loved it even more bc Adam is from Manchester, NH, one town over from where I lived in Bedford. Then he became a star on SNL, my favorite show.  This was a big deal.'
